Addressing the Commons on Tuesday, Mr Johnson said: "It is vital that President Putin understands that what he is doing will be a disaster for Russia". He said that Russia will end up being poorer because of sanctions, will be more isolated, and has pariah status and no chance of hosting football tournaments. The Prime Minister announced restrictions on five Russian banks and three wealthy Russian individuals and said that more sanctions will be applied if the situation escalates further. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES....  